                     |CKBChapter 12 - Partying
              |BKB-----------------------------------
     
     |WKBAt levels 1-5 you can form parties with other newbies to make
     your newbie experience more enjoyable. After level 6 you will
     only be able to party with players level 6 and up. 
     
     Party experience is shared based on the level of the players,
     and whether or not all members are present in the room where
     the experience was awarded. More experience is granted to
     those of higher level. Gold is split equally between all members.
     
     To form a party, go up to another unpartied person and use the
     |YKB'poffer' |WKBcommand.
     
     |BKBParty Commands:
     |MKOpstatus                   |BKB- |CKOLists members and other info.
     |MKOpsplit <amount>           |BKB- |CKOShares amount of gold with party.
     |MKOpautosplit <on|off>       |BKB- |CKOTurns on or off automatic gold split
     |MKOpleave                    |BKB- |CKOUse this to leave the party.
     |MKOpfollow <on|off>          |BKB- |CKOToggles following the party leader.
     |MKOpsay <message>            |BKB- |CKOSends a message to all members.
     |MKOepsay <message>           |BKB- |CKOEmotes a message to all members.
     |MKOpartyhist                 |BKB- |CKOShows the history of the party channel
  
     |WKBIf you're the party leader, you can also do the following:
     |MKOpoffer <member>           |BKB- |CKOAdds a member to your party. This can
                                 also be used by a person not in a
                                 party to form a new party.
     |MKOpboot <member>           |BKB - |CKORemoves a member from your party.
     |MKOpname <party_name>        |BKB- |CKOSets a party name (displayed in who).
     |MKOpleader <member>          |BKB- |CKOChanges the leader of the party.

     |WKBFor more information on any of these commands, use |RKB'help <command>'|WKB.
     General information on parties is listed in |RKB'help party'|WKB.
